  <how_to_use_section>
    <how_to_use>
      <how_to_use_steps>
        <step>Start Visual Studio and open the solution.</step>
        <step>Build the solution to make the DynamicDisplayHUD class library.</step>
        <step>Use this command in an application with a MapControl and a ToolbarControl, such as the MapControlApplication template included with the Visual Studio integration.</step>
        <step>Add both commands to the ToolbarControl. The commands can be found in the .NET Samples category with the names, Dynamic HUD and Toggle dynamic mode.</step>
        <step>Run the application, add, then click the Toggle dynamic mode command to switch into dynamic mode. </step>
        <step>Click Dynamic HUD to add the HUD to the map.</step>
        <step>Use the rotation tool to rotate the map (the HUD changes while the map rotates).</step>
      </how_to_use_steps>
    </how_to_use>
